; High-precision float display parity (issue #310).
;
; Before the fix, native printed doubles with "%g" (6 sig figs) and the VM
; with "%.6g" — both truncated, so this file could not have existed in the
; "shared display-format range". Now both paths route through the single
; shortest-round-trip formatter (eshkol_dtoa_shortest), so the VM and native
; agree BYTE-FOR-BYTE on full-precision values.
(display (sqrt 2.0)) (newline)
(display 3.141592653589793) (newline)
(display (/ 1.0 3.0)) (newline)
(display 1234567.0) (newline)
(display 4.75072e-11) (newline)
(display (number->string (sqrt 2.0))) (newline)
(display (number->string 0.1)) (newline)
(display 1e-10) (newline)
(display 1e308) (newline)
(display -0.0) (newline)
